dc_title_s: South America, Venezuela, La Guaira and approaches (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency Hydrographic/Topographic Center. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From surveys by U.S.S. Hannibal in 1939 and 1940 and a Venezuelan chart to 1985." Place names in Spanish with glossary in English. "Copyright 1994 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Includes compilation diagram. Insets: Catia la Mar. Scale 1:25,000 -- La Guaira. Scale 1:12,500. Georeferenced nautical chart. Map no. 24452. This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA).
